name: Calamari Bathe & Binge

reviews.review_text:
Located in front of Santana Beach Resort in Candolim, Calamari offers a prime beachfront dining experience. The restaurant's convenient location makes it easily accessible for both locals and tourists staying in the area.

Calamari in Goa is a fantastic place to enjoy a meal right by the beach. It's conveniently located with plenty of parking, and the restaurant itself is large and spacious, providing ample room for a comfortable dining experience. While there are a few shacks available, they tend to fill up quickly around sunset, so it's wise to arrive early if you want a prime spot.

We tried the Fish and Chips, and it was excellent. The fish was fresh, and the chips had the perfect amount of crispiness. The service was commendable, with friendly and attentive staff. However, the prices are a bit higher than what you might typically find in Goa these days, but the quality of the food and the overall experience make it worthwhile. In summary, Calamari is a great option for dining in Goa, especially if you're seeking a spacious and well-situated restaurant with delicious food.

It's lovely, they have a candle light set up with live music,a white set up, with big pedestal  fan installed, and small ceiling fan at each set up.  The area is wide enough to accommodate 100 people in one go.
People can enter right from the candolim beach itself, it has a beach entrance,
Taste is super delicious, but vegetarian dishes are limited.

Great view, very convenient location in candolim. I would suggest to reserve a table before going if you want to sit near the beach. The food is always a hit here and then portions are good too. Service was fast and professional. It's a very beautiful shack that's very well managed.

description:
### Discovering Calamari Bathe & Binge: A Beachfront Gem in Candolim

Calamari Bathe & Binge, nestled along the scenic coastline of Candolim, boasts an impressive rating of **4.4** based on nearly **9,000** reviews. Frequent tags that highlight the restaurant's appeal include "shack" with **229 mentions**, "band" at **113**, and "sunset" at **103**, underscoring its vibrant atmosphere and perfect locale for unwinding with good food and live music. As a Goan establishment with **62 mentions**, it captures the local essence while enticing visitors with its beachfront charm.

### Ambiance & Design

Set directly in front of the Santana Beach Resort, Calamari offers an inviting ambiance that captures the spirit of coastal dining. With a spacious setting that can accommodate up to **100 guests**, it features white decorative accents complemented by a warm candlelight setup—ideal for romantic evenings or friendly gatherings. The photos reveal high ceilings adorned with ceiling fans, ensuring comfort amidst the tropical warmth. A beach entrance allows guests to transition seamlessly from the sandy shores to their dining table, accentuating the restaurant's laid-back vibe. The live music that graces the space further enhances the atmosphere, making each visit a memorable experience.

![Calamari Bathe & Binge - Ambiance](https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/geougc-cs/AHRlGdm6tcJH43MDpehOqMZkXSCnyigka6AIL_wXSA-JSkc3ewMNntRfokUm2TbR8Bee3v6WTCDedJhNix8hhuNwGsm-Mg5Y7EwYrq9Yo25AW58ZPV5wLpdhLZ_mG6vp5VH_TvefCy6F=w375-h281-p)

### Menu & Culinary Experience

The culinary offerings at Calamari shine brightly, particularly its **Fish and Chips**, often praised for its fresh catch and crispy perfection. Guests have noted the generous portion sizes, which deliver both satisfaction and value. For those seeking local flavors, the menu features a selection of Goan specialties, albeit with a cautionary mention that vegetarian options are somewhat limited. The food’s presentation is not just appealing to the palate but also visually delightful, a detail beautifully captured in customer photos showing colorful plates against the backdrop of beach views.

![Fish and Chips at Calamari](https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/geougc-cs/AHRlGdm6tcJH43MDpehOqMZkXSCnyigka6AIL_wXSA-JSkc3ewMNntRfokUm2TbR8Bee3v6WTCDedJhNix8hhuNwGsm-Mg5Y7EwYrq9Yo25AW58ZPV5wLpdhLZ_mG6vp5VH_TvefCy6F=w375-h281-p)

### Customer Experience & Service

Reviews consistently highlight the friendly and attentive staff at Calamari, enhancing the overall dining experience. Guests recommend making reservations, especially if you desire seating that overlooks the beach during sunset—a breathtaking view that adds another layer of enjoyment to your meal. The efficiency of the service has garnered compliments, ensuring that diners can relax and savor their time without undue delay.

### Popularity & Overall Impressions

With nearly **9,000 ratings leading to a solid **4.4-star review**, Calamari Bathe & Binge stands out as a popular dining destination that resonates well with both locals and visitors. Social media has amplified its buzz, with many sharing experiences of sunset dinners and live music, further cementing its reputation as a local favorite. Although some mention that prices can be slightly higher compared to typical beach shacks, the consensus is that the quality of food and overall ambiance justify the cost.

### Conclusion

In conclusion, Calamari Bathe & Binge captures the spirit of Goan dining by the sea, melding delicious fare with an enjoyable atmosphere. Whether you’re seeking a romantic dinner with a view, a lively outing with friends, or just a wonderful place to unwind after a day on the beach, Calamari beckons with its charm and culinary delights. Don't miss the chance to indulge in a meal here while soaking in the sunset views—the perfect ending to any day in paradise.
